	<div class="About Us" id="AboutUs">
	<h2>About Us</h2>
		The Paediatrics speciality at The City Hospital is an integrated healthcare division 
		that aims to offer an optimally nurturing environment for your child, 
		including a range of inpatient paediatric facilities and specialised critical care. 
		The super-speciality division uses a team approach in which oncologists, cardiologists, 
		nephrologists, endocrinologists and clinical nurses, work together to deliver paediatric 
		treatments. The team uses advanced technology and latest research to deliver the most 
		appropriate, effective, personalized treatment for children.
		The Institute is a notable destination for all types of problems, such as congenital heart
		 defects, chronic kidney disease, sickle cell anaemia and type 1 diabetes in children.		
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="What we Treat" id="WhatweTreat?">
	<h2>What we Treat?</h2>
		At The City Hospital Division of Paediatrics, our mission is to offer a thorough, 
		specialised and organised approach to patient care and treatment. The centre constitutes 
		a skilled and experienced team of doctors and clinical nurses from various paediatric 
		specialities, for treating all types of paediatric disorders. 
		<br>
		<ul type="square">
		<li>Congenital Heart Defects
		<li>Paediatric Cancer
		<li>Chronic Kidney Disease
		<li>Sickle Cell Anaemia
		<li>Type 1 Diabetes
		<li>Paediatric Eye Conditions
		<li>Urinary Tract Infection
		<li>Chronic Otitis Media
		<li>Gastroenteritis
		<li>Pediatric Endocrinology
		</ul>
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="How we Treat" id="HowweTreat?">
	<h2>How we Treat?</h2>
	The Paediatrics speciality at the City Hospital works towards providing diagnosis, 
	analysis, treatment and rehabilitative care to neonates, infants, children and adolescents.
	 At City Hospital, our approach combines a team of endocrinologists, nephrologists, cardiologists, 
	 oncologists, gastroenterologists and urologists, who come together to discuss the best 
	 possible treatment options for any kind of paediatric problems. We have sophisticated 
	 technologies available for paediatric disorders, including IMRT, VCUG, and PET Scan.
	</div>
